on monday, apart from the supermarket, the couple visited a technology museum and the wilshire bullocks department store, where they were joined by a hollywood entourage that included lynn redgrave, george peppard and lloyd bridges
at the supermarket, the duchess cruised the aisles and paid particular attention to the deli section, pausing to examine sushi and stuffed chicken breasts but tasting only one item _ a dollop of coffee-toffee chip ice cream
she said she loved the pastry but was afraid to eat it,'' confided assistant bakery manager barbara huereque, who recognized a sister calorie-counter
both the duchess and duke tried their hand at decorating a cake. andrew produced a vague approximation of a red rose and she made a lopsided white rose, symbol of the house of york
the london stock exchange posted gains in early trading today, in line with rises in new york and tokyo
the financial times-stock exchange 100-share index was up 13.3 points, or 0.75 percent, at 1782.1 by midmorning. the index opened at 1781.1, up 12.2 points from monday's close
brokers said prices increased across the board before the official opening, but profit-takers emerged to erase some gains
