stella sablan reported to cupertino high school at 8:30 a.m. monday and was sent to the principal's office
her son, fred, repeatedly warned his mother she was supposed to call school authorities within 48 hours after he came home sick on feb. 18. stella, a 37-year-old corporate manager, said she kept forgetting
it was my fault,'' she said. ``i didn't call. for freddie to servie detention was just wrong
if we want the kids to respect the school rules, we'd better make sure they make sense,'' she added
