plaintiffs have failed to show ... that the consequence of fraud would be to invalidate enough signatures as to fall below the constitutional threshold'' for signatures necessary to force a recall, martone said. the recall backers had turned in about 80,000 more petition signatures than the minimum needed for a recall vote
